# Auto Git Push After Every Change

After completing **any** file edit or set of edits in this project, always run the following steps automatically without waiting to be asked:

1. **If `doca-v2.html` was edited** → copy it to `index.html` first: `Copy-Item doca-v2.html index.html`
2. `git add` **both** `doca-v2.html` and `index.html` (always add both together)
3. `git commit -m` with a short descriptive message (feat/fix/chore prefix)
4. `git push`

## Critical Rule: index.html = doca-v2.html

> `index.html` is what Vercel serves. `doca-v2.html` is the working file.
> **They must always be identical.** Every edit to `doca-v2.html` must be copied to `index.html` before committing.
> NEVER commit `doca-v2.html` without also updating `index.html`.

## Rules

- Use PowerShell syntax (semicolons, not `&&`)
- Run all commands in a single Shell call
- Commit message format: `type(scope): short description` (e.g. `feat(slide-14): add soft skills`)
- Do this at the end of every task, even small edits
- Never skip the push step

## Example

```powershell
cd "c:\CursorProjects\DOCA BLueField"; Copy-Item doca-v2.html index.html; git add doca-v2.html index.html; git commit -m "feat(slide-14): add soft skills section"; git push
```
